<br>
I was just checking out a wizard message board and was reading about class balancing.  One of the wizards there said that they were shocked that the mage class doesn't have a root/snare type spell at all.  This made me start thinking about that.  Every other pure caster has a root/snare type spell which allows them to escape hairy situations, but mages don't.  I began to think about the number of times I have died while running to zone or casting gate.<br>
<br>
I think I may have a possible solution I don't know if it has ever been addressed but I imagine it has.  Just like we can summon a ring of levitation why cant we summon some type of item that has maybe one or two charges of root (one making more sense <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ).  Make the casting time long so we cant summon one use it and then summon another before the root breaks.   Make it lore so we cant carry around a bag full, and make it no drop so you can not hand it to a melee (don't know if you can make a summoned item no drop).  This would allow mages that one chance to escape that we don't normally have.  <br>
<br>
I am sure there are many flaws with this idea but I don't know of any in particular. If you see any or anyway to improve reply and let me know.  I think it would be cool to have.  <p><a href=mailto:RavianVarior@hotmail.com><b>Ravian Varior</b></a> <a href=http://www.legionoffyre.net><b>{Legion of Fyre}</b></a><br><b>LVL 33 Erudite Mage</b><br><a href=http://pub17.ezboard.com/bxegony >Xegony</a>
