<br>
The Pet in a Bottle thing might help a little, but I hope it can be instacast or darn fast. I hope one can bottle a pet and make a new one if necessary. I'm curious how Monster pets are going to be affected by this (bottling). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/urozzyroz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>rozzyroz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 92<br> <font color=#333333>(10/1/02 10:25:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=375.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Root for Us</span><hr size=1> well when we did have the best pets i could see not having root, but now with pet power being sooo close i dont see why we couldnt have any defense spells. unless they make our pets head and shoulders above all other pets ,in terms of damage mitigation, root and other defense spells should be taken into consideration. sure one of our pets casts a root and another a stun, but how often can we get those to stick or be casted on the mob when we really need it? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=wezloc>WEZLOC</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 871<br> <font color=#333333>(10/1/02 10:31:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=375.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Root for Us</span><hr size=1> Well i would like root but oh well it isn't going to happen. However from the list of new aa skills looks like Verant is going to address a serious class balancing issue by being uninventive as normal and going to make us spend 30aa to get pets that zone with us. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
The bad part is this is a major class balancing issues for mages from lvls 4 to 60. We should have some form of root if it is no more then a lore summoned ring with 2 charges of enstill. That greatly limits our ability to keep mobs at bay while giving us some form or protection when pets go down. Hell give us enstill at lvl 55 or something. I am willing to say we should have it as a 51 spell but forcing us to never have protection outside of a pet is horrid. <br>
<br>
People saying well we not suppose to have root is crap also. At one time pets were not neutral, monks could not wield weapons, pets took 50% experience, burnout use to kill your pet and so on. Those things changed with the times and the same should happen with mages regarding Root. <br>
<br>
